f70e26bacf30379054627.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: The Pokemon Company\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"e712a1dd1dbf70e26bacf30379054627\" data-recommend-id=\"image://e712a1dd1dbf70e26bacf30379054627\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1080\" data-height=\"607\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Vaporeon talks to Jolteon \" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e  \u003cem\u003ePokémon TCG Pocket\u003c/em\u003e arrived this week on iPhone and Android, and it’s a surprisingly crisp and streamlined version of the card game after years of really bad alternatives. \u003cem\u003ePokémon\u003c/em\u003e is pretty much a license to print money, but \u003cem\u003eTCG Pocket\u003c/em\u003e does a great job of spotlighting what people love about about the game—the cards themselves—and getting most of the other stuff out of the way. Still, as a big fan of Marvel Snap, there are a few things I wish the mobile game would steal from Second Dinner’s 2022 comic book phenomenon.  — Ethan Gach\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-marvel-snap-rewards-card-1851686837\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-marvel-snap-rewards-card-1851686837\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"0c1d8b876b37fdce8c81895c5f0a31da\" data-recommend-id=\"image://0c1d8b876b37fdce8c81895c5f0a31da\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A screenshot of a trailer for Pokemon TCG Pocket, showing a full-art Squirtle card on the player\u0026#39;s phone.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A screenshot of a trailer for Pokemon TCG Pocket, showing a full-art Squirtle card on the player\u0026#39;s phone.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/0c1d8b876b37fdce8c81895c5f0a31da.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/0c1d8b876b37fdce8c81895c5f0a31da.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/0c1d8b876b37fdce8c81895c5f0a31da.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A screenshot of a trailer for Pokemon TCG Pocket, showing a full-art Squirtle card on the player\u0026#39;s phone.\" data-chomp-id=\"0c1d8b876b37fdce8c81895c5f0a31da\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"A screenshot of a trailer for Pokemon TCG Pocket, showing a full-art Squirtle card on the player\u0026#39;s phone.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/0c1d8b876b37fdce8c81895c5f0a31da.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Kotaku/ Nintendo / The Pokemon Company / DeNA\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"0c1d8b876b37fdce8c81895c5f0a31da\" data-recommend-id=\"image://0c1d8b876b37fdce8c81895c5f0a31da\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A screenshot of a trailer for Pokemon TCG Pocket, showing a full-art Squirtle card on the player\u0026#39;s phone.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eI’m \u003cem\u003ereally \u003c/em\u003eaverse to trading card games. Despite loving me some \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/tag/pokemon\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/tag/pokemon\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ePokémon\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cem\u003eYu-Gi-Oh\u003c/em\u003e as a kid and tween, I’ve largely kept my distance from them in the time since. I’ve played a few hands of \u003cem\u003eHearthstone\u003c/em\u003e, I never touched \u003cem\u003eArtifact\u003c/em\u003e, and I am straight-up dogshit at any card game baked into an RPG, except for \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-queens-blood-card-expansion-dlc-1851331334\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-queens-blood-card-expansion-dlc-1851331334\"\u003eQueen’s Blood\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e in \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-review-ps5-1851276129\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-review-ps5-1851276129\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy VII Rebirth\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e. Maybe it’s all the stories I’ve seen of players spending exorbitant amounts of money to pull rare cards from booster packs, but the pastime seems dominated by greed and status more than the fun of the tactics and interplay between cards that I always valued.  — Moises Taveras\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-impressions-gacha-mobile-card-game-1851686829\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-impressions-gacha-mobile-card-game-1851686829\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
